<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-02T11:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-02T11:29:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/418</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-02T20:00:00+03:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 8, 11
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1462. Yesterday’s demonstration against Provisional Government
                                disappointing to projectors. Cossacks and loyal soldiers at 3 this
                                morning arrested 68 anarchists who had undisputed possession of
                                Durnovo Palace two months and who last evening compelled prison
                                keeper to release several criminals. This by order of Provisional
                                Government. Enthusiastic impromptu demonstration now being held
                                incited by decisive victory for Russian forces on southeast front,
                                9,000 prisoners taken. Outlook for Government more encouraging than
                                for weeks past.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>